main event: A flashing object was observed in the Pacific Ocean on May 29, 1964, flying from west to east at high speed.
interesting points: The object had a size and brightness comparable to a second magnitude star,The observation lasted approximately 1 minute,The object's elevation decreased from 30 degrees to 20 degrees during the sighting,Insufficient data was reported for the identification of the object,The sighting was part of military observations under Project 10073.
location: Pacific Ocean, Unknown Region, Unknown Country
